Ask HN: What is the best browser “new tab” hack that keeps you productive?
text: Dabbling for a long time with ways of staying more productive, I always felt the "new tab" (in Chrome, Firefox, etc.) has a lot of potential to be the front page to a GTD hack that could simplify one's focus and help stay productive. Curious to hear what the community have been using the "new tab" for (e.g. todo lists, integrations with trello/ms todo/google tasks, integration with emails/calendars, pomodoro timers, etc.).

text:
LLMs can now understand and process natural language.

I’m looking for problems that exist in the business space that could be solved by using LLMs like GPT-3.

For example, is there something that takes a lot of time that could be better utilized somewhere else?

Anything related to this is highly welcomed

text:
This account is now anonymous.
